				\begin{document}$$DE\, \% =(\frac{{C}_{o}-{C}_{t}}{{C}_{0}})\times 100$$\end{document}Here Co = initial pollutant concentration and Ct = pollutant concentration at time ‘t’ (min). Influence of different reaction conditions as catalyst dose, Co, pH of solution and reusability studies were also conducted on the selected best photocatalyst. For better insight into the degradation mechanism and to assess the active degrading species separate experiments were designed in lines with the optimal photocatalytic experiments with active species trapping agents. In these experiments t-butanol, p-benzoquinone (BQ) and ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA) were used as hydroxyl radical (•OH), superoxide radicals (•O2−) and holes (h+) scavengers, respectively.

